dropper
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a light, vertical fence post between the main fixed posts, attached to the wires only to keep them firm and evenlyspaced.Contrast -->standard, -->waratah.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date: 29/5/1912
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 33
Edition:
Quote: In the erection of a wire fence it isusual to put the posts in the ground at acomfortable distance apart, droppers beingused as intermediate attachments tothe wire to keep them from opening orcontracting so that animals are preventedfrom forcing their way between the wire.
